132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 24
S.P. 39 In Senate, January 8, 2025
Resolve, Authorizing the Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands
to Convey Public Land Parcels in Lincoln Plantation and Sandy
River Plantation
Submitted by the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry pursuant to Joint
Rule 204.
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on January 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BLACK of Franklin.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Preamble. The Constitution of Maine, Article IX, Section 23 requires that real estate
2 held by the State for conservation or recreation purposes may not be reduced or its uses
3 substantially altered except on the vote of 2/3 of all members elected to each House; and
4 Whereas, certain real estate authorized for conveyance by this resolve is under the
5 designations described in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 598-A; and
6 Whereas, the Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands within the Department of
7 Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry may sell or exchange lands with the approval of
8 the Legislature in accordance with the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 1851; now,
9 therefore, be it
10 Sec. 1. Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands authorized to convey
11 certain land in Lincoln Plantation. Resolved: That the Director of the Bureau of
12 Parks and Lands within the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry may by
13 quitclaim deed convey without covenant, on other terms and conditions as the director may
14 direct, the State's interest in 47 leased lots in Lincoln Plantation. The cost of a survey of
15 the property boundaries, if a survey is necessary, may be paid by the bureau and factored
16 into the purchase price, but the recording costs may not be paid by the bureau.
17 Sec. 2. Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands authorized to exchange
18 certain land in Sandy River Plantation. Resolved: That the Director of the Bureau
19 of Parks and Lands within the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry is
20 authorized to exchange a small leased parcel and additional land up to 0.25 acres in Sandy
21 River Plantation in a value-for-value transaction for a deeded right-of-way across an
22 adjacent parcel.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This resolve authorizes the Director of the Bureau of Parks and Lands within the
2255 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to implement land transactions at 2
2266 locations. The director is authorized to convey 47 leased lots in Lincoln Plantation.
2277 Proceeds from the sale must be used to purchase conservation land in Oxford County. In
2288 addition, the director is authorized to exchange a small leased parcel and additional land
2299 up to 0.25 acres in Sandy River Plantation in a value-for-value transaction for a deeded
3300 right-of-way across an adjacent parcel.
